==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tectibranchiata
<hw>Tec`ti*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>tectus</ets> (p. p. of <ets>tegere</ets> to
cover) + Gr. <?/ a gill.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order, or
suborder, of gastropod Mollusca in which the gills are usually situated
on one side of the back, and protected by a fold of the mantle. When
there is a shell, it is usually thin and delicate and often rudimentary.
The aplysias and the bubble shells are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tectibranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
